model.hed: 14 Sweet and Savory Ways to Use Fresh Figs
model.dek: Wrapping them in bacon is just the beginning.
model.promoHed: 14 Sweet and Savory Ways to Use Fresh Figs
model.body:
Now's the time to buy up all the fresh figs at the market. With this list, you'll definitely find a way to eat your way through them.

####1. Pair them with [salty smoky pork](http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/fresh-figs-with-bacon-and-goat-cheese-351591)####
Because the fruit's honeyed sweetness is a 'natch with stuff like bacon, pancetta and prosciutto. And the combo is heaven. 

####2. ...And bold or mild cheeses.####
From stinky blues to delicate goats, cheese is a natural partner for figs, making a fine starter or a not-too-sweet last course.

####3. Serve them over [yogurt](http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/yogurt-with-fresh-figs-honey-and-pine-nuts-51239840).####
It's a tasty way to get a few oohs and ahhs over breakfast or dessert. 

####4. Or [pizza](https://epicurious.conde.io/recipes/food/views/grilled-sausage-and-fig-pizza-with-goat-cheese-360090)!####
Because fig-topped pizza is To. Die. For.

####5. Add them to [salads](http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/fresh-fig-prosciutto-and-arugula-salad-with-parmesan-shavings-15180).####
Figs' rich texture and honeyed sweetness partner especially well with hearty or peppery greens, like kale or arugula. 

####6. [Roast](http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/dulce-de-leche-ice-cream-with-honey-orange-roasted-figs-232897) or [Poach](http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/sambuca-poached-figs-with-ricotta-and-pine-nuts-105435) fresh figs.####
And discover a whole new layer of luscious, melty texture.


####7. Go [Ottolenghi-style](http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/roasted-sweet-potatoes-fresh-figs-51115420)!
Because if Ottolenghi's doing it, it's gotta be good.


+++landscape


[#image: /photos/54b07fa61cc76a014cfa9c59]||||||


text in callout


+++

####8. Simmer figs into [preserves](https://epicurious.conde.io/recipes/food/views/spiced-fig-preserves-15606).####  
It's a perfect way to save the fruits of that short season.

####9. Then use those preserves to take your next [grilled cheese sandwich](http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/grilled-artisan-cheddar-fig-jam-sandwich-51201620) to a whole 'nother level.####
Because warm cheesy bread with figs = happiness.


+++landscape


[#image: /photos/54ad57b719925f464b3b4cf4]||||||


text in callout


+++

#### 10. Roast them with honey, olive oil, flaky sea salt and freshly ground black pepper.#### 
Eat them as is, and be grateful. Or go ahead and serve them atop ice cream or [panna cotta](http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/lemon-pannacotta-with-lemon-marmalade-365158), or with [pound cake](http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/citrus-pound-cake-241214) and mascarpone. Because you can.

#### 11...Or bake them into cakes.#### 
[Like this one!](http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/plum-and-polenta-cake-51119620)

#### 12. Serve them over waffles, pancakes [or crepes](https://epicurious.conde.io/recipes/food/views/cornmeal-crepes-with-figs-and-pears-51187090).#### 
It's the easiest way to dress up a lazy Sunday.

+++landscape


[#image: /photos/54ad74ce19925f464b3b8133]||||||


text in callout


+++

#### 13. Roast them alongside chicken or [duck](https://epicurious.conde.io/recipes/food/views/roast-ducks-with-potatoes-figs-and-rosemary-51259450).#### 
Figs and roast meats play especially well with fresh savory herbsâ€”try tucking a couple branches of rosemary or thyme into the roasting pan. 

#### 14. Or use them to make toasts or [tartines](https://epicurious.conde.io/recipes/food/views/rustic-fig-serrano-ham-hazelnut-tartines-51126420).#### 
It just doesn't get any prettier. Or more delicious.  


+++landscape


[#image: /photos/54b064d8fca98987608b24a9]||||||


text in callout


+++
